  "prompt": "How can I get rid of a pimple on the bridge of my nose?",
  "response": "Here are some methods to help get rid of a pimple on the bridge of your nose:\n\n1. Spot treatments\n- Use over-the-counter acne treatments containing salicylic acid or benzoyl peroxide\n- Apply tea tree oil (diluted)\n- Use a hydrocolloid patch\n\n2. Home remedies\n- Apply ice to reduce inflammation\n- Use a warm compress to help draw out pus\n- Apply honey or aloe vera for healing properties\n\n3. Hygiene practices\n- Keep the area clean\n- Don't touch or pick at the pimple\n- Use oil-free, non-comedogenic skincare products\n- Change pillowcases frequently\n\n4. Additional tips\n- Stay hydrated\n- Maintain a balanced diet\n- Manage stress levels\n- Get enough sleep\n\n5. When to seek help\n- If the pimple is large, painful, or doesn't improve after a week\n- If you have recurring acne\n- If the pimple shows signs of infection\n\nAvoid squeezing or popping the pimple, as this can cause scarring and spread bacteria.",
